You continue your way through the dark hallways of the fortress.

Muffled voices get through the massive stone walls, way more than you'd expect during the middle of the night.

Fortunately none come as close as your last encounter with the guards, unwanted attention is the last thing-{nw}

No point in denying if they already found my lockpicks, eh?

They won't let me go no matter what.

But maybe they'll let you go if I tell them-{nw}

You hear a key turning and the door locking.

Now that you are left alone you feel the exhaustion again. Not wanting to sit on the cold floor, you feel for the chair you had seen.

As you sit down and rest your head on the table your eyelids get heavier and heavier.{w=1.0}.{w=1.0}.{nw}

Finally the hand pulls away.

Still, nobody dares to move a muscle.

The monster is most likely still{wait=0.5}{nw}

The vicious claws slice through the air, fast enough for you to sense the wind on your cheeks.

In the flurry of arms an opening presents itself. The monster tries to reach over its shoulder to get Morrok.

You charge the creature. A well placed bodycheck might topple- {w=1.0} {nw}

With the dagger clenched in your hand, you approach the monster. 

It is still occupied with Caya.

If you can sneak up to it from behind you might be able-{w=0-5}{nw}
